    "This reasoning is based on the hypothesis that the current deep learning paradigm can, perhaps with some moderate adjustments, lead to AGI.",
    "In essence, there are reasons to think that increasing the scale of current transformer models, like the most powerful current LLMs (e.g.",
    "GPT-4), suffices for AGI.",
    "The scale of the model is determined by the number of parameters comprising the model, the size of the dataset used to train the model and the amount of compute used for training.",
    "The first reason is that, in LLMs, scaling has led to massive increases in pre-existing capacities and the emergence of qualitatively new capacities (Wei et al. 2022)."
